Make sure npm is installed in your machine
Install all the packages needed:
npm install
In order to run this application:
npm start


------------------------------------------------------------------------------
//-y option instruct npm to create the package.json configuration file with
default settings, without prompting you for any options.
npm init -y

run the:
npm run tsc
 command, the transpiled hello_server.js file will be saved in the build directory.
Start web server with:
node build/hello_server.js

Need to have Node's type-definition file to prevent TypeScript compilation errors.
npm i @types/node --save

To minimize manual coding, installing Express.
A Node framework that provides a set of features required by all web applications.
npm install express --save

Save the express in the package.json file:
npm i @types/express --save

Go to localhost:8000